Abia State Governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu has solicited for the support of Ututu people as he strives to ensure even development in all communities in the state. He also urged them to comply to all COVID-19 preventive protocols for their safety and well being of others. Speaking at a fundraising event at St Paul’s Catholic church, Ututu in the Arochukwu Local Government Area of the state on Sunday, Ikpeazu assured that his government will continue to assist communities to achieve their developmental initiatives. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Governor who spoke through the provost of Abia State College of Education Technical Arochukwu (ASCETA) Dr. Phillips Nto, said his love for Ututu people encouraged him to appoint their sons into positions of authority in the state. He said apart from the provost, he also appointed Special Advisers and education secretary from the community, while the newly elected deputy chairman of Arochukwu LG ,Hon Cletus Nwankwo hails from there too. S’Africa Passes 30,000 Confirmed COVID-19 Deaths, With 434 In Just One Day Ekene Dili Chukwu’s Son Dies Of COVID-19 In Lagos In his remarks, the provost, Dr Phillips Nto, a former Commissioner for Information in the state, described Ikpeazu as a special friend of Ututu community through his appointments and sitting of projects. He attributed the giant strides he has recorded in ASCETA to the support and financial assistance of the Governor and praised him for always identifying with the people of Ututu. In his remarks, the parish priest of St Paul’s Catholic church, Ututu, Rev Father Livinus Okamgba appreciated the governor for his support and prayed for the success of his administration. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION